---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout name="surreal number playground" back wide>
  <p class="surreal-intro">Surreal numbers are born from cuts <code>{'{ left | right }'}</code>. Every left option must be smaller than every right option; the number created is the <em>simplest</em> value between them.</p>

  <section class="surreal-panel" id="surreal-app">
    <article class="surreal-card surreal-wide">
      <h2>birthdays</h2>
      <p class="surreal-note">Start at day 0 with <code>0 = {'{ | }'}</code>. Each new day inserts the simplest missing dyadic fractions between older numbers.</p>
      <div class="surreal-days" id="surreal-days" aria-live="polite"></div>
    </article>

    <form class="surreal-card" id="surreal-cut-form">
      <h2>make a cut</h2>
      <p class="surreal-note">Pick older values. The playground finds the simplest surreal number between the two sides.</p>
      <label>
        left options, comma-separated
        <input id="surreal-left" type="text" value="0" placeholder="e.g. 0, 1/2" />
      </label>
      <label>
        right options, comma-separated
        <input id="surreal-right" type="text" value="1" placeholder="e.g. 1, 2" />
      </label>
      <button class="toolbar-button" type="submit">create</button>
      <div class="surreal-output" id="surreal-cut-output" aria-live="polite"></div>
    </form>

    <article class="surreal-card">
      <h2>try these</h2>
      <div class="surreal-examples">
        <button class="toolbar-button" type="button" data-left="" data-right="">{'{ | }'} = 0</button>
        <button class="toolbar-button" type="button" data-left="0" data-right="">{'{ 0 | }'} = 1</button>
        <button class="toolbar-button" type="button" data-left="" data-right="0">{'{ | 0 }'} = -1</button>
        <button class="toolbar-button" type="button" data-left="0" data-right="1">{'{ 0 | 1 }'} = 1/2</button>
        <button class="toolbar-button" type="button" data-left="1" data-right="2">{'{ 1 | 2 }'} = 3/2</button>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="surreal-card surreal-wide">
      <h2>why it is nice</h2>
      <p>With one recursive rule, surreals contain integers, fractions, real numbers, infinities like <code>ω = {'{ 0, 1, 2, ... | }'}</code>, and infinitesimals like <code>1/ω</code>. The finite part shown here is already a tiny universe: numbers appear when there is room for them to be the simplest choice.</p>
    </article>
  </section>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .surreal-intro,
  .surreal-note,
  :global(.surreal-muted) {
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .surreal-panel {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(min(100%, 22rem), 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .surreal-wide {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
  }

  .surreal-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    padding: 1rem;
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .surreal-card h2 {
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .surreal-card label {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .surreal-card input {
    width: 100%;
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--fg);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 0.35rem 0.45rem;
  }

  .surreal-days {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  :global(.surreal-day) {
    display: block;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    padding-top: 0.75rem;
    min-width: 0;
    max-width: 100%;
  }

  :global(.surreal-day strong) {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  :global(.surreal-values) {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(4.25rem, 1fr));
    gap: 0.35rem;
    min-width: 0;
    max-width: 100%;
  }

  :global(.surreal-pill) {
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 999px;
    padding: 0.05rem 0.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    white-space: nowrap;
    min-width: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    text-overflow: ellipsis;
  }

  .surreal-output {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .surreal-examples {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }
</style>

<script>
  import '../scripts/surreal.ts';
</script>
